Why Ceiling Division?
Pizzas must be ordered whole - you can't buy 1.5 pizzas. When total slices needed isn't evenly divisible by 8, you need one extra pizza.

Mathematical Breakdown
For ceiling(a/b) with integers: (a + b - 1) / b
Here: a = totalSlices, b = 8, so (totalSlices + 8 - 1) / 8 = (totalSlices + 7) / 8

import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;
import java.io.*;

class Codechef
{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
	{
		// your code goes here
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        
        int g = sc.nextInt();
        
        int B = b + 1;
        
        int a1 = (4 * B) + (3 * g);
        
        int a2 = (a1 + 7) / 8;
        
       System.out.println(a2);
	}
}

